---
// Compact bridge path reminder — mirrors in-app guides
---
<section class="deposit-section">
  <div class="deposit-card">
    <h3 class="section-title">Quick path</h3>
    <ol class="path-list">
      <li><strong>Connect MetaMask</strong> · then <strong>Register L1 address</strong> (L1 · MetaMask header / Overview)</li>
      <li><strong>Warthog → Sub-wallets</strong> · fund sub → sweep &amp; lock WART as capacity</li>
      <li><strong>Overview → WLIQ</strong> · mint shares against available capacity</li>
      <li><strong>Burn / vault → main</strong> · free collateral, multi-sig withdraw</li>
    </ol>
    <p class="hint">
      Native WART uses Sub-wallets (not L1 ERC-20 portals). ETH/CTSI/USDC portals stay on the L1 tab.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .deposit-section {
    margin: 1.75rem 0 2.5rem;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .section-title {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #ffecb3;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .deposit-card {
    background: color-mix(in srgb, #1a1a1a 85%, #000);
    border-radius: 14px;
    padding: 1rem 1.15rem 1.15rem;
    max-width: 40rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    border: 1px solid #333;
  }
  .path-list {
    text-align: left;
    max-width: 32rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding-left: 1.15rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    opacity: 0.92;
  }
  .path-list li + li {
    margin-top: 0.3rem;
  }
  .hint {
    margin: 0.85rem 0 0;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    opacity: 0.65;
    line-height: 1.45;
  }
</style>
